Eve Rachel Hall and Daniel Adam Shacknai, were married last evening at the Brooklyn Botanic Garden.

Rabbi Martin Freedman, the bridegroom's stepfather, performed the ceremony.

Ms. Hall, 41, is keeping her name. She is a consultant, in Manhattan, on the development of television programs for children. She graduated from Wesleyan University and received a master's degree in education from Harvard.

She is the daughter of Helene and Norman Hall of Great Neck, N.Y. Her father, who is the president of the the board of the Public Access Television Corporation in Lake Success, N.Y., is the producer and director of ''New Playwrights,'' a cable access show. Her mother is a reference librarian at Great Neck Library.

Mr. Shacknai, also 41, is known as Don. He is the deputy commissioner for intergovernmental affairs at the New York City Fire Department in Brooklyn. He graduated cum laude from Bucknell University and received a law degree magna cum laude from Cornell. His mother, Shirley Shacknai Freedman, lives in Wayne, N.J., where she retired as an English teacher from Schuyler Colfax Junior High School. His father, the late Shai Shacknai, was the rabbi of Temple Beth Tikvah in Wayne.